  "prompt": "What are the problems faced by the people of sikkim?",
  "response": "Sikkim, a small northeastern state in India, faces several challenges:\n\n1. Geographical Challenges:\n- Mountainous terrain making infrastructure development difficult\n- Prone to landslides and earthquakes\n- Limited flat land for agriculture and construction\n\n2. Economic Issues:\n- Limited job opportunities\n- Dependence on tourism and agriculture\n- Low industrial development\n- High unemployment rate\n\n3. Infrastructure Problems:\n- Poor road connectivity in remote areas\n- Limited transportation options\n- Inadequate healthcare facilities\n- Underdeveloped telecommunications infrastructure\n\n4. Environmental Concerns:\n- Vulnerability to climate change\n- Deforestation\n- Soil erosion\n- Biodiversity conservation challenges\n\n5. Social Issues:\n- Limited higher education opportunities\n- Migration of youth to other states\n- Limited skill development programs\n- Low per capita income\n\n6. Agricultural Challenges:\n- Small landholdings\n- Limited agricultural mechanization\n- Dependence on traditional farming methods\n- Vulnerability to natural disasters\n\n7. Demographic Challenges:\n- Sparse population\n- Low population density\n- Aging population\n- Limited human resources\n\n8. Healthcare Limitations:\n- Limited medical facilities in rural areas\n- Shortage of specialized medical professionals\n- Challenging healthcare access in remote regions\n\nThese challenges require comprehensive and sustainable development strategies.",
